N2  - The article explores the relationship between transcendental meditation and productivity at work. Using six measures of productivity, mediators reported they experienced increased job satisfaction, better performance and better relationships with supervisors and co-workers. Data support the proposition that productivity gains are an increasing function of structural level. Mediators reported that their gains in job satisfaction and performance and improved interpersonal relationships were more position than those of mediators who work at low levels of organizations.
