N2  - The article presents a comparison of believers and non-believers in the existence of social equality in New Zealand with work conditions of high and low participation in decision making, in relation to participative management theory. The author presents data from a national investigation of job satisfaction, motivation and labor turnover of wage-earning employees in the country. The results support the author's belief that there is a positive relationship between high participation and high job satisfaction.
